SIMPLE: divot
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Divot
<hw>Div"ot</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A thin,
oblong turf used for covering cottages, and also for fuel.</def>
<mark>[Scot.]</mark> <rj><au>Simmonds.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Golf)</fld> <def>a small piece of turf gouged out
of the ground by the head of a golf club when making a stroke; <as>as,
all divots should be replaced</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Divulgate</ent>⟦br⟧
